content:
Prepare for changes that affect the way you import data from custom sources within Salesforce Maps Advanced. This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

Support for importing data from custom sources retires on May 16, 2025. An alternative method provides an option for storing the data in Salesforce.

First create a custom object so that you can store your data in its records, and then import your data by using the Data Import Wizard. Next, create a base object that represents your newly created custom object. Finally, create your marker layers that include the imported data for your sales reps.

See also: Create a Custom Object, Import Data with the Data Import Wizard, Create Base Objects to Plot on Maps, Create Marker Layers
title: Changes in Custom Data Sources for Salesforce Maps
